article.description: Steve Cluley threw for 262 yards and two touchdowns to lead William & Mary to a 31-17 victory over Towson on Saturday.
article.headline: Cluley with 2 TD passes, William & Mary beats Towson 31-17
article.linkText: Cluley with 2 TD passes, William & Mary beats Towson 31-17
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- Steve Cluley threw for 262 yards and two touchdowns to lead William & Mary to a 31-17 victory over Towson on Saturday. Cluley threw scoring strikes of 5 and 35 yards to Kevin Hart, and four passes for 88 yards, including a 51-yarder to Daniel Kuzjak. Kendell Anderson ran for a score, and Zach Fetters recovered a fumble and returned it 36 yards for a touchdown for William & Mary (8-2, 6-1 Colonial Athletic Association). Darius Victor ran for 96 yards with touchdown runs of 1 and 13 yards to lead Towson (6-4, 4-3). Victor scored with four minutes left to pull the Tigers to 24-17. William & Mary recovered the ensuing onside kick and drove 50 yards in seven plays, capped by Anderson's 3-yard touchdown run with 1:11 left to seal if for the Tribe.
